## Step 3: Set up the equation based on the given probability
The total probability of drawing two balls of the same color is the sum of the probabilities of drawing two red balls and two blue balls. This gives us the equation: $(8/15) \times (r/(r+9)) + (7/15) \times (9/(r+9)) = 151/300$.

## Step 4: Simplify and solve the equation
First, simplify the equation: $(8r + 63)/(15(r+9)) = 151/300$. Cross-multiply to get: $300(8r + 63) = 151 \times 15(r+9)$. Expanding both sides gives: $2400r + 18900 = 2265r + 20385$. Rearranging the equation to solve for $r$: $2400r - 2265r = 20385 - 18900$, which simplifies to $135r = 1485$. Solving for $r$ gives: $r = 1485 / 135 = 11$.

